<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 17 at 12:53AM EST  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...AN AREA OF HEAVY SNOW WILL AFFECT PARTS OF
ONTARIO...LIVINGSTON...
WYOMING...ORLEANS...WAYNE...GENESEE...MONROE...NIAGARA...AND
NORTHERN ERIE COUNTIES...
HAZARDS...An area of EXTREMELY heavy snow which can rapidly reduce
visibility to less than a quarter of a mile. This area of heavy snow
is producing extremely heavy snow at the rate of over 4 inches
inches per hour.
LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 1250 AM EST, the leading edge of the
heavy snow was from Niagara Falls to Brockport moving north at 20
MPH.
LOCATIONS IMPACTED INCLUDE...
Buffalo, Rochester, Greece, Cheektowaga, Irondequoit, Niagara Falls,
West Seneca, North Tonawanda, Clarence, Chili, Lockport, Batavia,
Kenmore, Depew, Amherst, Tonawanda, Lancaster, Brockport, Geneseo and
East Rochester.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 390 between exits 8 and 12.
Interstate 90 between exits 53 and 44.
SAFETY INFO...
The snow will accumulate so rapidly that it will be extremely
difficult for the road crews to keep the roads clear. Delay travel
in the next couple hours if possible.
&amp;&amp;</description>
